    "While KRR-based methods achieve competitive performance, the graph kernel in KRR is memory-intensive and does not scale well with large-scale graphs.",
    "Distribution matchingbased methods perform well on smaller datasets, whereas gradient matching-based methods are more effective on larger datasets.",
    "Generalization.",
    "We adhere to the settings commonly used in most GC studies and assess the generalization of GC methods across various GNN models for the node classification task.",
    "The GNN models evaluated include GCN [97], SGC [17], SAGE [10], APPNP [99], Cheby [100] and GAT [101]."
